sentences: Robert Charles Goldsboro (born January 18, 1941) is an American pop and country singer-songwriter.

He had a string of pop and country hits in the 1960s and 1970s, including his signature No. 1 hit "Honey", which sold over 1 million copies in the United States, and the UK top-10 single "Summer (The First Time)".
